Fifteen people have been killed and 14 others were injured last night in Numa village, Andaha Town, in Akwanga Local Government Area of Nasarawa State. Report shows that the people were killed by armed bandits when they were celebrating at a party late in the night. Details soon.  UPDATE: 15 people killed, 14 injured in Nasarawa State Nyako puts N25m prize on gunmen 11 killed in fresh clashes between farmers, herders in Benue Nasarawa boundary